text: If you work for the #NHS, you can get free access to a range of wellbeing apps to help with: mindfulness reducing stress building resilience getting better sleep. View our full offer of wellbeing support for #OurNHSPeople at http://people.nhs.uk. #TheBigNightIn

'I knew if I needed to call again someone was there for me.' Mental Health Nurse Shaila shares how the wellbeing support line for #OurNHSPeople helped her when she returned to the frontline to help her colleagues tackle #coronavirus. #TheBigNightIn http://people.nhs.uk
As we gear up for another #ClapForCarers at 8pm, we'd like to thank people across the country who continue to support #OurNHSPeople in their brilliant and unique ways. #ThankYouNHS
We'd also like to say a huge thank you to all the volunteers from @samaritans, @hospiceUK and @giveusashout who have given a whopping 50,000 hours of their time to help with supporting #OurNHSPeople.

It's more important than ever that #OurNHSPeople have support. If you’re a member of NHS staff finding it difficult to cope and would like to speak to a trained professional about your mental health and wellbeing — call, text or visit http://people.nhs.uk. #TheBigNightIn

Thank you for the support from so many, including @TeamINEOS — the first company to make new PPE following the Government’s call to arms. They’ve produced hand sanitisers, at a rate of 1 million standard and pocket-bottle hand sanitisers a month, in ten days! #ThankYouThursday

It’s so inspiring to see teams across the country pulling together to help the NHS fight #coronavirus — like the amazing @HIOWAA, who are volunteering their free time to support #OurNHSPeople at @UHSFT’s emergency department. #ThankYouNHS

Looking after your mental health while you stay home because of #coronavirus isn’t always easy — you may feel frustrated, anxious or miss loved ones. Discover helpful tips on managing your mental wellbeing, with #EveryMindMatters. https://www.nhs.uk/oneyou/every-mind-matters/

If you, or someone you know needs to shield at home because of #coronavirus — you can get support with things like grocery and medication deliveries, and regular friendly phone calls from #NHSVolunteerResponders by calling 08081963646. http://www.nhsvolunteerresponders.org.uk
If you, or someone you know needs to shield at home because of #coronavrirus, you can get help from #NHSVolunteerResponders by calling 08081963646.

From today, millions of vulnerable people and their families will be able to directly call on the army of #NHSVolunteerResponders — to get support with shopping and medication deliveries, and regular friendly phone calls. https://www.england.nhs.uk/2020/04/vulnerable-people-get-direct-line-to-nhs-volunteer-army/

Giving blood counts as essential travel, and the NHS still needs your donations! Blood donation saves lives, so if you’re fit and well, please #KeepDonating. #coronavirus https://www.blood.co.uk/news-and-campaigns/news-and-statements/coronavirus-update/

We love this video of staff from @DarentValleyHsp celebrating as newly-engaged radiographer and colleague Paul leaves intensive care, after making a full recovery from #coronavirus. Congratulations, Paul and #ThankYouNHS!

Keeping a regular sleeping pattern, exercising and talking about your worries to loved ones are some of the ways you can keep on top of your #MentalHealth while you stay home because of #coronavirus. For more helpful tips, visit #EveryMindMatters. https://www.nhs.uk/oneyou/every-mind-matters/coronavirus-covid-19-anxiety-tips/

Annette's daughter had said her last goodbyes when her mum was taken into intensive care with #coronavirus, but after 17 days, we are so pleased to see the moment Annette receives a guard of honour at @WorcsAcuteNHS as she leaves the unit to continue her recovery. #ThankYouNHS

Routine immunisations for children and pregnant women are continuing during the COVID-19 outbreak. If you or a member of your household has symptoms, you should not attend your appointment - call the number on your letter to rearrange. Read more at https://bit.ly/3aDbCl2

Our new telephone helpline offers psychological advice to people across Lanarkshire who are experiencing anxiety, low mood or distress in relation to the Covid-19 coronavirus pandemic. Call 01698 687567. This week the helpline is open 8am-4pm Mon-Fri. https://www.nhslanarkshire.scot.nhs.uk/nhs-lanarkshire-launches-psychological-well-being-helpline/

Karen Goudie, chief nurse at Monklands, is encouraging her colleagues, patients and friends to try to stay positive during these difficult times. https://www.nhslanarkshire.scot.nhs.uk/protecting-our-most-at-risk-people-during-covid-19/

Staying indoors & social distancing mean lots of changes in our routines. This can have a negative effect on our mental wellbeing. Creating a daily routine helps everyone at home to keep a sense of calm and order. There are some ideas to help on NHSinform

Lanarkshire’s health and social care partners are working together to keep their most vulnerable people safe in a multi-agency ‘shielding’ exercise. https://www.nhslanarkshire.scot.nhs.uk/protecting-our-most-at-risk-people-during-covid-19/

Chest Heart and Stroke Scotland are helping those isolating. They have have over 4,000 volunteers who can call, collect shopping, dog walking and pick up prescriptions. https://www.chss.org.uk/coronavirus/i-need-help/

Hi, we wouldn’t comment on individual staff members or groups but would stress safety is our top priority. Robust testing procedures are in place for any symptomatic staff member or their families. The test only works on someone who has symptoms.
NHS Lanarkshire's gender based violence team helped to create this short video for staff. The resource will help to support women at risk of gender based violence.

A new telephone helpline is offering psychological support and advice to people across Lanarkshire during the Coronavirus (Covid-19) pandemic. The helpline aims to those who are experiencing anxiety, low mood or other mental health issues in relation to Covid-19. 01698 687567.

I was overwhelmed by so much attention for my birthday today from friends from all over the world. HRH Michael of Kent, Patron & Jean-Yves Ollivier, Chair of the Brazzaville Foundation, & many other world luminaries made this day a special one to remember. Thank you, everyone.

I wish each of you a Happy & Prosperous New Year. I call for a renewed spirit of unity in Uganda and in the rest of the world. Let us focus on what we have in common and join hands in creating a beautiful future of greater prosperity and greater and durable peace for humanity.

I send warmest greetings & best wishes to all those celebrating Xmas around the world. I hope that the gospel of Christ is reflected in every aspect of joy, love & peace. Let us come together, whatever our faith, united in the universal values we share, to build a better world.

I started to cry. This dove had come here to watch over me. So we filmed her singing her song & I’m sending her out to you. With love, Stevie Nicks p.s. She’s been here for days. I think she’s here for good

Several days ago, outside my room, I started to hear the sound of a bird singing the same thing over and over. One little Ahhh~ and then three OOH’s~ over and over again. I thought it was an owl, but a friend said, “No, that’s a dove!”
As you well know, I was very taken with that whole picture and went on to write “Edge of Seventeen.” But over the last 40 years I can honestly say, I have never heard a dove sing~ until now.

In 1980 I was flying home from Phoenix Arizona and I was handed a menu that said, “The white wing dove sings a song that sounds like she’s singing ooh, ooh, ooh. She makes her home here in the great Saguaro cactus that provides shelter and protection for her…”
